HEADWORD: Plaything
<hw>Play"thing`</hw> <pr>(pl⟦amac⟧"th⟦icr⟧ng`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A thing to play with; a toy; anything that serves to
amuse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A child knows his nurse, and by degrees the <qex>playthings</qex>
of a little more advanced age.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Playtime</ent>⟦br⟧
